# What the Docker daemon does NOT send into the build context.
# Keeps the build fast and the runtime image clean (no secrets, no test
# artefacts, no IDE / native-platform trees, no local DB snapshots).

# --- node + build outputs ---
node_modules/
dist/
build/
coverage/
*.log

# --- VCS + IDE ---
.git/
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store

# --- env files (NEVER ship secrets via the image layer) ---
.env
.env.*

# --- native platforms (not part of the server image) ---
android/
ios/

# --- forensic snapshots + local DB ---
uploads/
prisma/dev.db
temp/

# --- misc ---
*.zip
# NOTE: `public/landing.html` is intentionally NOT excluded — Vite's build copies
# it from public/ to dist/landing.html, which Express serves at /landing on prod.
# If we ever move the landing to a separate CDN, exclude it here.
